<OBJECTS>
Object_Heading	Object_Text	aRequirementObjectType	Section_number	ID.Status	aResponsibility	a_EB_PO_Status	a_ZF_PO_Status
1 File Management			1	1_Heading.0	Not relevant		
	This section covers requirements for opening, saving, creating and closing project files.	information	1.1	PO-FILE-INFO-001.0	Not relevant		
1.1 Open Project			1.1	1_1_Heading.0	Not relevant		
	The system shall support opening project files in the formats: .mpp, .xml, .mpt, .mpx via the MPXJ UniversalProjectReader.	functional requirement	1.1.1	PO-FILE-001.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	When opening a project file, the system shall load all tasks, resources, assignments, dependencies, calendars, and baseline data from the file.	functional requirement	1.1.2	PO-FILE-002.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	After opening a project, the system shall automatically load the associated sidecar files: <basename>.timeline.json (timeline pin data) and <basename>.splits.json (task split data).	functional requirement	1.1.3	PO-FILE-003.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The system shall display the project title in the window title bar after opening.	functional requirement	1.1.4	PO-FILE-004.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
1.2 Save Project			1.2	1_2_Heading.0	Not relevant		
	The system shall save the project in MSPDI XML format (.xml) via MPXJ MSPDIWriter.	functional requirement	1.2.1	PO-FILE-005.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The system shall support Save (Ctrl+S, overwrites current file) and Save As (opens file dialog to choose new location).	functional requirement	1.2.2	PO-FILE-006.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	On save, the system shall write all sidecar files: .timeline.json and .splits.json alongside the project file.	functional requirement	1.2.3	PO-FILE-007.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The system shall mark the project as dirty (unsaved) whenever any data is modified and clear the dirty flag after a successful save.	functional requirement	1.2.4	PO-FILE-008.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
1.3 New Project			1.3	1_3_Heading.0	Not relevant		
	The system shall create a new empty project when the user chooses File → New.	functional requirement	1.3.1	PO-FILE-009.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	When creating a new project, the system shall open the Project Information dialog to collect the project start date and end date, which are mandatory.	functional requirement	1.3.2	PO-FILE-010.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	If the user cancels the Project Information dialog on new project, the new project shall be discarded.	functional requirement	1.3.3	PO-FILE-011.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	When creating a new project, the system shall automatically create a default calendar named "Standard (Deutschland)" containing German national public holidays for a range of (current year − 2) to (current year + 12) and set it as the project default calendar.	functional requirement	1.3.4	PO-FILE-018.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	After creating the default holiday calendar, the system shall display an "Install Optional Holiday Calendars" dialog that allows the user to select additional German federal state calendars and country calendars (France, India, Romania, China, Japan) to install. All checkboxes shall be unchecked by default.	functional requirement	1.3.5	PO-FILE-019.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	German state calendars installed during new project setup shall be derived from the "Standard (Deutschland)" calendar (via setParent()) and shall store only the state-specific extra public holidays not present in the national calendar.	functional requirement	1.3.6	PO-FILE-020.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	Country holiday calendars installed during new project setup (France, India, Romania, China, Japan) shall be standalone calendars with default working hours independent of the standard calendar.	functional requirement	1.3.7	PO-FILE-021.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	When creating a new project, the system shall initialise the project currency settings (symbol, code, decimal digits, and symbol position) from the operating-system locale monetary settings, falling back to MPXJ defaults if the locale cannot be determined.	functional requirement	1.3.8	PO-FILE-026.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
1.4 Close Project			1.4	1_4_Heading.0	Not relevant		
	The system shall provide a File → Close menu item to close the current project.	functional requirement	1.4.1	PO-FILE-012.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	Before closing a project with unsaved changes, the system shall prompt the user to save, discard, or cancel.	functional requirement	1.4.2	PO-FILE-013.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	After closing a project, all views shall be cleared and editing actions disabled.	functional requirement	1.4.3	PO-FILE-014.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
1.5 Project Information			1.5	1_5_Heading.0	Not relevant		
	The system shall provide a Project Information dialog accessible from the menu that allows editing the project title, start date, finish date, and status date.	functional requirement	1.5.1	PO-FILE-015.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The project start date and finish date shall be stored as MPXJ project properties.	functional requirement	1.5.2	PO-FILE-016.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The system shall support Enterprise Custom Fields stored as MPXJ enterprise fields on the summary task (UID=0), making per-project configuration portable across teams.	functional requirement	1.5.3	PO-FILE-017.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The Project Information → Project tab shall default the Start Date and Finish Date fields to the current date when no value is stored in the project (e.g. when opening the dialog for a newly created project).	functional requirement	1.5.4	PO-FILE-022.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The Project Information → Project tab shall default the Status Date field to the current date when no value is stored.	functional requirement	1.5.5	PO-FILE-023.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The Project Information → Project tab shall not display a "Current Date" field; the current system date is not configurable and does not require user input.	functional requirement	1.5.6	PO-FILE-024.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
	The Project Information → Calendar tab Default Start Time field shall default to 08:00 and Default Finish Time shall default to 17:00 when no value is stored in the project.	functional requirement	1.5.7	PO-FILE-025.0	Not relevant	approved	aligned
</OBJECTS>
